article.headline: Bowling Green 103, Urbana 78
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Ron Lewis scored 34 points and John Reimold added 22 points and nine rebounds in Bowling Green's 103-78 season-opening win over Urbana on Friday night. Josh Almanson scored 18 points for the Falcons, who outscored the Blue Knights (1-4) 17-8 over the final 4:47 of the first half to take a 51-43 lead. Urbana never got closer than nine points after halftime. Lewis scored eight points during the key run, starting the surge with two free throws to erase Urbana's 35-34 lead. Lewis hit two more free throws and also scored on two dunks during the run. Lewis made 9-of-15 shots from the floor -- 2-for-4 from 3-point range -- and connected on 14-of-15 free throws. The Falcons shot 57 percent from the floor (35-for-61) and went 26-for-30 at the foul line. Urbana shot just 44 percent (28-for-64) but made 9-of-25 3-pointers. Jarrod Brumbaugh led the Blue Knights with 18 points and Antonio Davis scored 17.
